text: Behold the foules of the ayre, that they sow not, neither reape, nor gather into barnes: and your heauenly father feedeth them.
verse_text: Biholde ye the foulis of the eire, for thei sowen not, nethir repen, nethir gaderen in to bernes; and youre fadir of heuene fedith hem. Whether ye ben not more worthi than thei?

text: And the thirde part of the creatures, which were in the sea, and had life, died, and the thirde part of shippes were destroyed.
verse_text: et mortua est tertia pars creaturae eorum, quae habebant animas in mari, et tertia pars navium interiit.

text: And the thirde part of the creatures, which were in the sea, and had life, died, and the thirde part of shippes were destroyed.
verse_text: and the thyrde parte of the see tourned to bloud and the thyrde parte of the creatures which had lyfe dyed and the thyrde part of shippes were destroyed.

text: Domine exercituum, Deus Israel, qui sedes super cherubim, tu es Deus solus omnium regnorum terrae: tu fecisti caelum et terram.
verse_text: O Lord of hosts, God of Israel, who sittest upon the cherubims, thou alone art the God of all the kingdoms of the earth, thou hast made heaven and earth.

text: fac vindictam in homine isto et exercitu ejus, et cadant in gladio: memento blasphemias eorum, et ne dederis eis ut permaneant.
verse_text: Be avenged of this man, and his army, and let them fall by the sword: remember their blasphemies, and suffer them not to continue any longer.

text: But yet reioyce not in this, that the spirits are subiect vnto you; but reioyce in this, that your names are written in Heauen.
verse_text: Neverthelesse in this reioyse not that the spretes are vnder youre power: but reioyse be cause youre names are wrytten in heaven.

text: For first of all, I deliuered vnto you that which I receiued, how that Christ died for our sinnes, according to the Scriptures,
verse_text: Tradidi enim vobis in primis quod et accepi: quoniam Christus mortuus est pro peccatis nostris secundum Scripturas:

text: He that heareth you, heareth me; and he that despiseth you, despiseth me. And he that despiseth me, despiseth him that sent me.
verse_text: He that herith you, herith me; and he that dispisith you, dispisith me; and he that dispisith me, dispisith hym that sente me.

text: Speake vnto all the Congregation of the children of Israel, and say vnto them, Ye shalbe holy, for I the Lord your God am holy.
verse_text: Speke thou to al the cumpenye of the sones of Israel, and thou schalt seie to hem, Be ye hooli, for Y am hooli, youre Lord God.

text: Thou shalt therefore keepe the Commandements, and the Statutes, and the Iudgements, which I command thee this day, to doe them.
verse_text: Custodi ergo praecepta et caeremonias atque judicia, quae ego mando tibi hodie ut facias.

text: And he said to him: If they heare not Moyses and the Prophets, neither if one shal rise againe from the dead, wil they beleeue.
verse_text: And he seide to hym, If thei heren not Moises and prophetis, nethir if ony of deed men rise ayen, thei schulen bileue to hym.

text: Or howe sayest thou to thy brother, Suffer me to cast out the mote out of thine eye, and beholde, a beame is in thine owne eye?
verse_text: Or hou seist thou to thi brothir, Brothir, suffre I schal do out a mote fro thin iye, and lo! a beem is in thin owne iye?

text: And the shekel shalbe twentie gerahs, and twentie shekels, and fiue and twentie shekels and fifteene shekels shalbe your Maneh.
verse_text: Siclus autem viginti obolos habet: porro viginti sicli, et viginti quinque sicli, et quindecim sicli, mnam faciunt.

text: Sed iniquitates vestrae diviserunt inter vos et Deum vestrum; et peccata vestra absconderunt faciem ejus a vobis, ne exaudiret.
verse_text: But your iniquities have divided between you and your God, and your sins have hid his face from you that he should not hear.

text: Let euery man as hee hath receiued the gift, minister the same one to another, as good disposers of the manifolde grace of God.
verse_text: Unusquisque, sicut accepit gratiam, in alterutrum illam administrantes, sicut boni dispensatores multiformis gratiae Dei.

text: The statutes of the Lord are right and reioyce the heart: the commandement of the Lord is pure, and giueth light vnto the eyes.
verse_text: Hi in curribus, et hi in equis; nos autem in nomine Domini Dei nostri invocabimus.

text: And ouer the Arke were the glorious Cherubims, shadowing the mercie seat: of which things we will not nowe speake particularly.
verse_text: Over the arcke were the cherubis of glory shadowynge the seate of grace. Of which thynges we wyll not now speake perticularly.

text: And when hee came downe to Cesarea, he went vp to Hierusalem: and when he had saluted the Church, he went downe vnto Antiochia.
verse_text: and came vnto Cesarea: and ascended and saluted the congregacion and departed vnto Antioche

text: And hee said vnto him, If they heare not Moses and the Prophets, neither will they be perswaded, though one rose from the dead.
verse_text: And he seide to hym, If thei heren not Moises and prophetis, nethir if ony of deed men rise ayen, thei schulen bileue to hym.

text: Dixitque David ad Joab et ad principes populi: Ite, et numerate Israel a Bersabee usque Dan: et afferte mihi numerum ut sciam.
verse_text: And David said to Joab, and to the rulers of the people: Go, and number Israel from Bersabee even to Dan, and bring me the number of them that I may know it.

text: Magnificavit ergo Dominus Salomonem super omnem Israel: et dedit illi gloriam regni, qualem nullus habuit ante eum rex Israel.
verse_text: And the Lord magnified Solomon over all Israel: and gave him the glory of a reign, such as no king of Israel had before him.

text: And when hee had saide this, there was a dissension betweene the Pharises and the Sadduces, so that the multitude was deuided.
verse_text: Et cum haec dixisset, facta est dissensio inter pharisaeos et sadducaeos, et soluta est multitudo.

text: Vnto ye morow after the seuenth Sabbath shall ye nomber fiftie dayes: then yee shall bring a newe meate offring vnto the Lord.
verse_text: Even unto the marrow after the seventh week be expired, that is to say, fifty days, and so you shall offer a new sacrifice to the Lord.

text: But with him that standeth here with vs this day before the Lord our God, and also with him that is not here with vs this day:
verse_text: sed cunctis praesentibus et absentibus.

text: And thou shalt giue the Leuites vnto Aaron and to his sonnes: for they are giuen him freely from among the children of Israel.
verse_text: And thou schalt yyue bi fre yifte the Leuytis to Aaron and hise sones, to whiche thei ben youun of the sones of Israel.

text: And the praier of faith shal saue the sicke: and our Lord shal lift him vp: and if he be in sinnes, they shal be remitted him.
verse_text: and the prayer of fayth shall save the sicke and the lorde shall rayse him vp: and yf he have committed synnes they shalbe forgeuen him.

text: For Kings, and for all that are in authoritie, that we may leade a quiet and a peaceable life, in all godlinesse and honestie.
verse_text: pro regibus, et omnibus qui in sublimitate sunt, ut quietam et tranquillam vitam agamus in omni pietate, et castitate:

text: Brethren, be not children in vnderstanding, but as concerning maliciousnes be children, but in vnderstanding be of a ripe age.
verse_text: Fratres, nolite pueri effici sensibus, sed malitia parvuli estote: sensibus autem perfecti estote.

text: I am the Lord your God, which haue brought you out of the lande of Egypt, to giue you the lande of Canaan, and to be your God.
verse_text: I am the Lord your God, who brought you out of the land of Egypt, that I might give you the land of Chanaan, and might be your God.

text: I am the Lord your God, which haue brought you out of the lande of Egypt, to giue you the lande of Canaan, and to be your God.
verse_text: Ego Dominus Deus vester, qui eduxi vos de terra AEgypti, ut darem vobis terram Chanaan, et essem vester Deus.

text: And thou shalt giue the Leuites vnto Aaron and to his sonnes: for they are giuen him freely from among the children of Israel.
verse_text: Dabisque dono Levitas

text: Blessed are ye, when men shall reuile you, and persecute you, and shal say all manner of euill against you falsly for my sake.
verse_text: Ye schulen be blessid, whanne men schulen curse you, and schulen pursue you, and shulen seie al yuel ayens you liynge, for me.

text: Being of one mind one toward another. Not minding high things, but consenting to the humble. Be not wise in your owne conceit.
verse_text: idipsum invicem sentientes: non alta sapientes, sed humilibus consentientes. Nolite esse prudentes apud vosmetipsos:

text: And after the Diuel was cast out, the dumme man spake, and the multitudes marueled saying: Never was the like seene in Israel.
verse_text: Et ejecto daemonio, locutus est mutus, et miratae sunt turbae, dicentes: Numquam apparuit sic in Israel.

text: Concerning the rest of the actes of Zachariah, behold, they are written in the booke of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel.
verse_text: Now the rest of the acts of Zacharias, are they not written in the book of the words of the days of the kings of Israel?

text: Concerning the rest of the actes of Zachariah, behold, they are written in the booke of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel.
verse_text: Reliqua autem verborum Zachariae, nonne haec scripta sunt in libro sermonum dierum regum Israel?

text: But notwithstanding I say to you, that it shal be more tolerable for the land of Sodom in the day of iudgement, then for thee.
verse_text: Verumtamen dico vobis, quia terrae Sodomorum remissius erit in die judicii, quam tibi.

text: But notwithstanding I say to you, that it shal be more tolerable for the land of Sodom in the day of iudgement, then for thee.
verse_text: But I say vnto you, that it shall be easier for them of the land of Sodom in the day of iudgement, then for thee.

text: Israel shall dwell in safety, and alone. The eye of Jacob in a land of corn and wine, and the heavens shall be misty with dew.
verse_text: Israel then shall dwell in safetie alone: the fountaine of Iacob shalbe vpon a land of corne and wine, also his heauens shall drop downe deaw.

text: Quia antequam sciat puer reprobare malum et eligere bonum, derelinquetur terra quam tu detestaris a facie duorum regum suorum.
verse_text: For before the child know to refuse the evil, and to choose the good, the land which thou abhorrest shall be forsaken of the face of her two kings.

text: For all that is borne of God, ouercommeth this world: and this is that victorie that hath ouercome this world, euen our faith.
verse_text: Quoniam omne quod natum est ex Deo, vincit mundum: et haec est victoria, quae vincit mundum, fides nostra.

text: principem super quinquaginta, et honorabilem vultu et consiliarium, et sapientem de architectis, et prudentem eloquii mystici.
verse_text: The captain over fifty, and the honourable in countenance, and the counsellor, and the architect, and the skillful in eloquent speech.

text: Therefore by the woorkes of the Lawe shall no flesh be iustified in his sight: for by the Lawe commeth the knowledge of sinne.
verse_text: quia ex operibus legis non justificabitur omnis caro coram illo. Per legem enim cognitio peccati.

text: Therefore by the woorkes of the Lawe shall no flesh be iustified in his sight: for by the Lawe commeth the knowledge of sinne.
verse_text: For by the lawe commeth the knowledge of synne.

text: Being of one mind one toward another. Not minding high things, but consenting to the humble. Be not wise in your owne conceit.
verse_text: Be of lyke affeccion one towardes another. Be not hye mided: but make youreselves equall to the of the lower sorte. Be not wyse in youre awne opinions.

text: And said vnto them, Thus is it written, and thus it behoued Christ to suffer, and to rise againe from the dead the third day,
verse_text: And he seide to hem, For thus it is writun, and thus it bihofte Crist to suffre, and ryse ayen fro deeth in the thridde dai;

text: And from sixty yeere olde and aboue, if he be a male, then thy price shalbe fifteene shekels, and for the female ten shekels.
verse_text: Sexagenarius et ultra masculus dabit quindecim siclos: femina, decem.

text: Euery one as he hath receiued grace, ministring the same one toward another: as good dispensers of the manifold grace of God.
verse_text: Unusquisque, sicut accepit gratiam, in alterutrum illam administrantes, sicut boni dispensatores multiformis gratiae Dei.

text: which in tyme past were not a people yet are now the people of God: which were not vnder mercye but now have obteyned mercye.
verse_text: Which sometime not a people: but now the people of God. Which not hauing obtained mercie: but now hauing obtained mercie.

text: Spiritus ubi vult spirat, et vocem ejus audis, sed nescis unde veniat, aut quo vadat: sic est omnis qui natus est ex spiritu.
verse_text: The wynde bloweth where he listeth and thou hearest his sounde: but canst not tell whence he cometh and whether he goeth. So is every man that is boren of the sprete.

text: Ipsi autem non cognoverunt cogitationes Domini, et non intellexerunt consilium ejus, quia congregavit eos quasi foenum areae.
verse_text: But they have not known the thoughts of the Lord, and have not understood his counsel: because he hath gathered them together as the hay of the floor.

text: Dicit eis: Venite et videte. Venerunt, et viderunt ubi maneret, et apud eum manserunt die illo: hora autem erat quasi decima.
verse_text: He sayde vnto them: come and se. They came and sawe where he dwelt: and abode with him that daye. For it was about the tenthe houre.

text: But of that day and houre knoweth no man, no, not the Angels which are in heauen, neither the Sonne himselfe, but the Father.
verse_text: De die autem illo vel hora nemo scit, neque angeli in caelo, neque Filius, nisi Pater.

text: Locutus est autem angelus Domini ad Eliam, dicens: Descende cum eo: ne timeas. Surrexit igitur, et descendit cum eo ad regem,
verse_text: And the angel of the Lord spoke to Elias, saying: Go down with him, fear not. He arose therefore, and went down with him to the king,

text: Then he saith to the man: Stretch forth thy hand, and he stretched it forth, and it was restored to health euen as the other.
verse_text: Tunc ait homini: Extende manum tuam. Et extendit, et restituta est sanitati sicut altera.

text: Then he saith to the man: Stretch forth thy hand, and he stretched it forth, and it was restored to health euen as the other.
verse_text: Then sayde he to the man: stretch forth thy had. And he stretched it forthe. And it was made whole agayne lyke vnto the other.

text: For I was an hungred, and ye gaue me meate: I thirsted, and ye gaue me drinke: I was a stranger, and ye tooke me in vnto you.
verse_text: esurivi enim, et dedistis mihi manducare: sitivi, et dedistis mihi bibere: hospes eram, et collegistis me:

text: The sunne shal be turned into darkenes, and the moone into the bloud before the great and manifest day of our Lord doth come.
verse_text: The sunne shalbe turned into darknes and the mone into bloud before that greate and notable daye of the Lorde come.

text: And they asked him, and saide vnto him, Why baptizest thou then, if thou be not that Christ, neither Elias, nor that Prophet?
verse_text: Et interrogaverunt eum, et dixerunt ei: Quid ergo baptizas, si tu non es Christus, neque Elias, neque propheta?

text: For assuredly I say vnto you, til Heauen and earth passe, one iot, or one tittle shal not passe the Law, til al be fulfilled.
verse_text: Whosoeuer therefore shall breake one of these least commandements, and teach men so, he shall be called the least in the kingdome of heauen: but whosoeuer shall obserue and teach them, the same shall be called great in the kingdome of heauen.

text: Pavl an Apostle of Jesvs Christ by the will of God, to the Saints, which are at Ephesus, and to ye faithfull in Christ Iesus:
verse_text: Paulus Apostolus Jesu Christi per voluntatem Dei, omnibus sanctis qui sunt Ephesi, et fidelibus in Christo Jesu.

text: Pavl an Apostle of Jesvs Christ by the will of God, to the Saints, which are at Ephesus, and to ye faithfull in Christ Iesus:
verse_text: Paul an Apostle of Iesu Christ by the will of God. To the saynctes which are at Ephesus and to them which beleve on Iesus Christ.

text: And shall deliuer him to the Gentiles, to mocke, and to scourge, and to crucifie him, but the third day he shall rise againe.
verse_text: et tradent eum gentibus ad illudendum, et flagellandum, et crucifigendum, et tertia die resurget.

text: From the endes of the earth will I crye vnto thee: when mine heart is opprest, bring me vpon the rocke that is higher then I.
verse_text: Nonne Deo subjecta erit anima mea? ab ipso enim salutare meum.

text: Vnto me the lest of all sayntes is this grace geven that I shuld preache amonge the gentyls the unsearchable ryches of Christ
verse_text: Unto mee, who am lesse then the least of all Saints, is this grace giuen, that I should preach among the Gentiles the vnsearchable riches of Christ,

text: And the Lord answered him: Is the hand of the Lord unable? Thou shalt presently see whether my word shall come to pass or no.
verse_text: To whom the Lord answeride, Whether the hond of the Lord is vnmyyti? riyt now thou schalt se, wher my word schal be fillid in werk.

text: And shall deliuer him to the Gentiles, to mocke, and to scourge, and to crucifie him, but the third day he shall rise againe.
verse_text: And thei schulen bitake hym to hethene men, for to be scorned, and scourgid, and crucified; and the thridde day he schal rise ayen to lijf.

text: And shall deliuer him to the Gentiles, to mocke, and to scourge, and to crucifie him, but the third day he shall rise againe.
verse_text: and shall delyvre him to the getils to be mocked to be scourged and to be crucified: and the thyrd daye he shall ryse agayne.

text: Unde et vos inter ceteros festos dies, hanc habetote diem, et celebrate eam cum omni laetitia, ut et in posterum cognoscatur,
verse_text: Wherefore you shall also count this day among other festival days, and celebrate it with all joy, that it may be known also in times to come,

text: In die illa projiciet homo idola argenti sui, et simulacra auri sui, quae fecerat sibi ut adoraret, talpas et vespertiliones.
verse_text: In that day a man shall cast away his idols of silver, and his idols of gold, which he had made for himself to adore, moles and bats.

text: And his seruants caried him in a charet to Ierusalem, and buried him in his sepulchre with his fathers in the citie of Dauid.
verse_text: Et imposuerunt eum servi ejus super currum suum, et tulerunt in Jerusalem: sepelieruntque eum in sepulchro cum patribus suis in civitate David.

text: And they asked him, and saide vnto him, Why baptizest thou then, if thou be not that Christ, neither Elias, nor that Prophet?
verse_text: And they axed him and sayde vnto him: why baptisest thou then yf thou be not Christ nor Helyas nether a Prophet?

text: Let them alone, they be the blinde leaders of the blinde: and if the blinde leade ye blinde, both shall fall into the ditche.
verse_text: Suffre ye hem; thei ben blynde, and leederis of blynde men. And if a blynd man lede a blynd man, bothe fallen doun in to the diche.

text: Haec in proverbiis locutus sum vobis. Venit hora cum jam non in proverbiis loquar vobis, sed palam de Patre annuntiabo vobis:
verse_text: These thinges have I spoken vnto you in proverbes. The tyme will come when I shall no moare speake to you in proverbes: but I shall shewe you playnly from my father.

text: And the children of Amram, Aaron, and Moses and Miriam. And the sonnes of Aaron, Nadab, and Abihu, and Eleazar, and Ithamar.
verse_text: Filii Amram: Aaron, Moyses, et Maria. Filii Aaron: Nadab et Abiu, Eleazar, et Ithamar.

text: (For the halfe that perteined vnto the Congregation, was three hundreth thirtie and seuen thousand sheepe and fiue hundreth,
verse_text: De media vero parte, quae contigerat reliquae multitudini, id est, de ovibus trecentis triginta septem millibus quingentis,

text: (For the halfe that perteined vnto the Congregation, was three hundreth thirtie and seuen thousand sheepe and fiue hundreth,
verse_text: But out of the half that fell to the rest of the multitude, that is to say, out of the three hundred thirty-seven thousand five hundred sheep,

text: And when he had said these things, there rose dissension between the Pharisees and Sadducees; and the multitude was deuided.
verse_text: And when he had so sayde ther arose a debate bitwene the Pharisayes and the Saduces and the multitude was devided.

text: Et respondit rex Ptolemaeus, dicens: Felix dies, in qua reversus es ad terram patrum tuorum, et sedisti in sede regni eorum.
verse_text: And king Ptolemee answered, saying: Happy is the day wherein thou didst return to the land of thy fathers, and sattest in the throne of their kingdom.

text: We are weried in the way of iniquitie and perdition, and haue walked hard wayes, but the way of our Lord we haue not knowen.
verse_text: Lassati sumus in via iniquitatis et perditionis, et ambulavimus vias difficiles: viam autem Domini ignoravimus.

text: And Reaiah the sonne of Shobal begat Iahath, and Iahath begate Ahumai, and Lahad: these are the families of the Zoreathites.
verse_text: And Raia the son of Sobal beget Jahath, of whom were born Ahumai, and Laad. These are the families of Sarathi.

text: Because the creature also shall be deliuered from the bondage of corruption into the glorious libertie of the sonnes of God.
verse_text: quia et ipsa creatura liberabitur a servitute corruptionis in libertatem gloriae filiorum Dei.

text: Who then is a faithfull seruaunt and wise, whom his master hath made ruler ouer his household, to giue them meate in season?
verse_text: Quis, putas, est fidelis servus, et prudens, quem constituit dominus suus super familiam suam ut det illis cibum in tempore?

text: Then let him offer with ye bullocke a meate offring of three tenth deales of fine floure, mingled with halfe an Hin of oyle.
verse_text: dabis per singulos boves similae tres decimas conspersae oleo, quod habeat medium mensurae hin:

text: And the chiefe steward tooke Seraiah the chiefe Priest, and Zephaniah the second Priest, and the three keepers of the doore.
verse_text: And the general of the army took Seraias the chief priest, and Sophonias the second priest, and three doorkeepers.

text: And there are three, which beare record in the earth, the spirit, and the water and the blood: and these three agree in one.
verse_text: Et tres sunt, qui testimonium dant in terra: spiritus, et aqua, et sanguis: et hi tres unum sunt.

text: And he went about the eleuenth houre, and found other standing idle, and sayd vnto them, Why stand ye here all the day idle?
verse_text: But aboute the elleuenthe our he wente out, and foond other stondynge; and he seide to hem, What stonden ye idel here al dai?

text: And as a vesture shalt thou folde them vp, and they shall be changed: but thou art the same, and thy yeeres shall not faile.
verse_text: et velut amictum mutabis eos, et mutabuntur: tu autem idem ipse es, et anni tui non deficient.

text: Non est priorum memoria; sed nec eorum quidem quae postea futura sunt erit recordatio apud eos qui futuri sunt in novissimo.
verse_text: There is no remembrance of former things: nor indeed of those things which hereafter are to come, shall there be any remembrance with them that shall be in the latter end.

text: And there are three, which beare record in the earth, the spirit, and the water and the blood: and these three agree in one.
verse_text: For there are thre which beare recorde (in erth:) the sprete and water and bloud: and these thre are one.

text: Doe not abhorre vs: for thy Names sake cast not downe the throne of thy glory: remember and breake not thy couenant with vs.
verse_text: Give us not to be a reproach, for thy name's sake, and do not disgrace in us the throne of thy glory: remember, break not thy covenant with us.

text: And from al things, from which ye could not be iustified by the Law of Moses, by him euery one that beleeueth, is iustified.
verse_text: in hoc omnis qui credit, justificatur.

text: We see now by a glasse in a darke fort: but then face to face. Now I know in part: but then I shal know as also I am knowen.
verse_text: Videmus nunc per speculum in aenigmate: tunc autem facie ad faciem. Nunc cognosco ex parte: tunc autem cognoscam sicut et cognitus sum.

text: Whereof I am a minister, according to the dispensation of God, which is giuen mee vnto you ward, to fulfill the word of God,
verse_text: wherof I am made a minister acordynge to the ordinaunce of god which ordinaunce was geven me vnto you warde to fulfill the worde of god

text: Whereof I am a minister, according to the dispensation of God, which is giuen mee vnto you ward, to fulfill the word of God,
verse_text: cujus factus sum ego minister secundum dispensationem Dei, quae data est mihi in vos, ut impleam verbum Dei:

text: All the cities which yee shall giue to the Leuites, shalbe eight and fourtie cities: them shall ye giue with their suburbes.
verse_text: That is, in all forty-eight with their suburbs.

text: qui scriptus es in judiciis temporum, lenire iracundiam Domini, conciliare cor patris ad filium, et restituere tribus Jacob.
verse_text: Who art registered in the judgments of times to appease the wrath of the Lord, to reconcile the heart of the father to the son, and to restore the tribes of Jacob.

text: Et cognovit Judas, et exiit obviam illi: et percussit, et occidit illum: et ceciderunt vulnerati multi, et reliqui fugerunt.
verse_text: And Judas understood it, and went forth to meet him: and he overthrew him, and killed him: and many fell down slain, the rest fled away.

text: And whereby ye are saued, if ye keepe in memorie, after what maner I preached it vnto you, except ye haue beleeued in vaine.

verse_text: No man hath sene God at eny tyme. The only begotte sonne which is in the bosome of the father he hath declared him.

text: Now in the third yeere of Hoshea, sonne of Elah King of Israel, Hezekiah the sonne of Ahaz king of Iudah began to reigne.
verse_text: In the third year of Osee the son of Ela king of Israel, reigned Ezechias the son of Achaz king of Juda.

text: But go your wayes & learne what it is, I wil mercie, & not not sacrifice. For I am not come to cal the iust, but sinners.
verse_text: But go ye, and lerne what it is, Y wole merci, and not sacrifice; for I cam, not to clepe riytful men, but synful men.

text: And the foure beasts said, Amen, and the foure and twentie Elders fell downe and worshipped him that liueth for euermore.
verse_text: And the .iiii. bestes sayd: Amen. And the .xxiiii. elders fell apon their faces and worshypped him that lyveth for ever more.

text: And when the euen was come, there came a riche man of Arimathea, named Ioseph, who had also himselfe bene Iesus disciple.
verse_text: But whanne the euenyng was come, ther cam a riche man of Armathi, Joseph bi name, and he was a disciple of Jhesu.

text: Et auferetur zelus Ephraim, et hostes Juda peribunt; Ephraim non aemulabitur Judam, et Judas non pugnabit contra Ephraim.
verse_text: And the envy of Ephraim shall be taken away, and the enemies of Juda shall perish: Ephraim shall not envy Juda, and Juda shall not fight against Ephraim.

text: Then came his Disciples, and said to him: Dost thou know that the Pharisees, when they heard this word, were scandalized?
verse_text: Thanne hise disciplis camen, and seiden to hym, Thou knowist, that, if this word be herd, the Farisees ben sclaundrid?

text: This people draweth neere vnto me with their mouth, and honoureth me with the lips, but their heart is farre off from me.
verse_text: and seide, This puple honourith me with lippis, but her herte is fer fro me;

text: Now in the third yeere of Hoshea, sonne of Elah King of Israel, Hezekiah the sonne of Ahaz king of Iudah began to reigne.
verse_text: Anno tertio Osee filii Ela regis Israel, regnavit Ezechias filius Achaz regis Juda.

text: Without naturall affection, truce breakers, false accusers, intemperate, fierce, no louers at all of them which are good,
verse_text: vnkinde trucebreakers stubborn falce accusars ryatours fearce despisers of the which are good

text: And the tenth part of an Ephah of fine floure for a meate offering mingled with the fourth part of an Hin of beaten oyle.
verse_text: Ye schulen offre the tenthe part of ephi of floure, which be spreynt with pureste oile, and haue the fourthe part of hyn.

text: After the death of Saul, when Dauid was returned from the slaughter of the Amalekites and had beene two dayes in Ziklag,
verse_text: Factum est autem, postquam mortuus est Saul, ut David reverteretur a caede Amalec, et maneret in Siceleg duos dies.

text: THESE are the generations of the sonnes of Noe, Sem, Cham, and Iapheth: and children were borne to them after the floud.
verse_text: These ben the generaciouns of the sones of Noe, Sem, Cham, and Jafeth. And sones weren borun to hem aftir the greet flood.

text: Likewise also after supper he tooke the cup, saying, This cup is that newe Testament in my blood, which is shed for you.
verse_text: Lykewyse also when they had supped he toke the cup sayinge: This cup is the newe testament in my bloud which shall for you be shedde.

text: And at the ende of twentie yeeres, when Salomon had buylded the two houses, the house of the Lord, and the Kings palace,
verse_text: Expletis autem annis viginti postquam aedificaverat Salomon duas domos, id est, domum Domini, et domum regis

text: Oratio humiliantis se nubes penetrabit, et donec propinquet non consolabitur, et non discedet donec Altissimus aspiciat.
verse_text: The prayer of him that humbleth himself, shall pierce the clouds: and till it come nigh he will not be comforted: and he will not depart till the most High behold.

text: Then came his disciples, and saide vnto him, Perceiuest thou not, that the Pharises are offended in hearing this saying?
verse_text: Tunc accedentes discipuli ejus, dixerunt ei: Scis quia pharisaei audito verbo hoc, scandalizati sunt?

text: Then came his disciples, and saide vnto him, Perceiuest thou not, that the Pharises are offended in hearing this saying?
verse_text: Thanne hise disciplis camen, and seiden to hym, Thou knowist, that, if this word be herd, the Farisees ben sclaundrid?

text: Let no man when he is tempted, say that he is tempted of God. For God is not a tempter of euils, and he tempteth no man.
verse_text: Nemo cum tentatur, dicat quoniam a Deo tentatur: Deus enim intentator malorum est: ipse autem neminem tentat.

text: Afterward concupiscence when it hath conceiued, bringeth forth sinne. But sinne when it is consummate, ingendreth death.
verse_text: Deinde concupiscentia cum conceperit, parit peccatum: peccatum vero cum consummatum fuerit, generat mortem.

text: Domine, miserere nostri, te enim exspectavimus; esto brachium nostrum in mane, et salus nostra in tempore tribulationis.
verse_text: O Lord, have mercy on us: for we have waited for thee: be thou our arm in the morning, and our salvation in the time of trouble.

text: quoniam filii sanctorum sumus, et vitam illam expectamus, quam Deus daturus est his qui fidem suam numquam mutant ab eo.
verse_text: For we are the children of the saints, and look for that life which God will give to those that never change their faith from him.

text: But as many as receiued him, to them he gaue prerogatiue to be the sonnes of God, euen to them that beleeue in his Name.
verse_text: But hou many euer resseyueden hym, he yaf to hem power to be maad the sones of God, to hem that bileueden in his name; the whiche not of bloodis,

text: But as many as receiued him, to them he gaue prerogatiue to be the sonnes of God, euen to them that beleeue in his Name.
verse_text: Quotquot autem receperunt eum, dedit eis potestatem filios Dei fieri, his qui credunt in nomine ejus:

text: Omnes nos quasi oves erravimus, unusquisque in viam suam declinavit: et posuit Dominus in eo iniquitatem omnium nostrum.
verse_text: All we like sheep have gone astray, every one hath turned aside into his own way: and the Lord hath laid on him the iniquity of us all.

text: Surely goodnes and mercie shall followe me all the daies of my life: and I will dwell in the house of the Lord for euer.
verse_text: Haec est generatio quaerentium eum, quaerentium faciem Dei Jacob.

text: Preach the worde: be instant, in season and out of season: improue, rebuke, exhort with all long suffering and doctrine.
verse_text: praedica verbum, insta opportune, importune: argue, obsecra, increpa in omni patientia, et doctrina.

text: quibus vero vellent auxilio esse ut regnarent, regnabant: quos autem vellent, regno deturbabant: et exaltati sunt valde.
verse_text: That whom they had a mind to help to a kingdom, those reigned: and whom they would, they deposed from a kingdom: and they were greatly exalted.

text: yet now he hath reconciled in the body of his flesh by death, to present you holy & immaculate, and blameles before him:
verse_text: in the body of his flesshe thorowe deeth to make you holy vnblameable and with out faut in his awne syght

text: And the Disciples according as each man had, purposed euery one to send, for to serue the Brethren that dwelt in Iewrie:
verse_text: Then the disciples every man accordinge to his abilite purposed to sende socoure vnto the brethren which dwelt in Iewry.

text: Therefore Hezekiah gaue all the siluer that was found in the house of the Lord, and in the treasures of the Kings house.
verse_text: Deditque Ezechias omne argentum quod repertum fuerat in domo Domini et in thesauris regis.

text: my soule coueteth, and fainteth vnto the courtes of our Lord. My hart, and my flesh haue reioyced toward the liuing God.
verse_text: They haue taken craftie counsell against thy people, and haue consulted against thy secret ones.

text: Hereby shall ye know the Spirit of God, Euery spirit which confesseth that Iesus Christ is come in the flesh, is of God.
verse_text: Herby shall ye knowe the sprete of God. Every sprete that confesseth that Iesus Christ is come in the flesshe is of God.

text: THERFORE if you be risen with Christ, seeke the things that are aboue; where Christ is sitting on the right hand of God.
verse_text: Igitur, si consurrexistis cum Christo: quae sursum sunt quaerite, ubi Christus est in dextera Dei sedens:

text: Surely I haue behaued and quieted my selfe as a child that is weaned of his mother: my soule is euen as a weaned childe.
verse_text: sicut juravit Domino; votum vovit Deo Jacob:

text: Now these are the generations of the sonnes of Noah, Shem, Ham and Iapheth: vnto whom sonnes were borne after the flood.
verse_text: These ben the generaciouns of the sones of Noe, Sem, Cham, and Jafeth. And sones weren borun to hem aftir the greet flood.

text: His amplius, fili mi, ne requiras. Faciendi plures libros nullus est finis; frequensque meditatio, carnis afflictio est.
verse_text: More than these, my son, require not. Of making many books there is no end: and much study is an affliction of the flesh.

text: Rugitus ejus ut leonis; rugiet ut catuli leonum: et frendet, et tenebit praedam, et amplexabitur, et non erit qui eruat.
verse_text: Their roaring like that of a lion, they shall roar like young lions: yea they shall roar, and take hold of the prey, and they shall keep fast hold of it, and there shall be none to deliver it.

text: Being defamed, we intreate: we are made as the filth of the world, and are the off-scouring of all things vnto this day.
verse_text: blasphemamur, et obsecramus: tamquam purgamenta hujus mundi facti sumus, omnium peripsema usque adhuc.

text: For if we be planted with him to the similitude of his death, euen so shall we be to the similitude of his resurrection,
verse_text: For yf we be graft in deeth lyke vnto him: even so must we be in the resurreccion.

text: Necnon de Thebath et Chun urbibus Adarezer aeris plurimum, de quo fecit Salomon mare aeneum, et columnas, et vasa aenea.
verse_text: Likewise out of Thebath and Chun, cities of Adarezer, he brought very much brass, of which Solomon made the brazen sea, and the pillars, and the vessels of brass.

text: For he is our God, and we are the people of his pasture, and the sheepe of his hand: to day if yee will heare his voyce,
verse_text: Afferte Domino, patriae gentium, afferte Domino gloriam et honorem;

text: Qui despicit proximum suum peccat; qui autem miseretur pauperis beatus erit. Qui credit in Domino misericordiam diligit.
verse_text: He that despiseth his neighbour, sinneth: but he that sheweth mercy to the poor, shall be blessed. He that believeth in the Lord, loveth mercy.

text: Tribulation and anguish shalbe vpon the soule of euery man that doeth euill: of the Iewe first, and also of the Grecian.
verse_text: Tribulatio et angustia in omnem animam hominis operantis malum, Judaei primum, et Graeci:

text: For if we be planted with him to the similitude of his death, euen so shall we be to the similitude of his resurrection,
verse_text: Si enim complantati facti sumus similitudini mortis ejus: simul et resurrectionis erimus.

text: For if the ministringe of condempnacion be glorious: moche more do the the ministracion of rightewesnes excede in glory.
verse_text: For if the ministration of condemnation bee glory, much more doth the ministration of righteousnesse exceed in glorie.

text: for kynges and for all that are in auctorite that we maye live a quyet and a peasable life in all godlines and honestie.
verse_text: For Kings, and for all that are in authoritie, that we may leade a quiet and a peaceable life, in all godlinesse and honestie.

text: And foure vndersetters were vpon the foure corners of one base: and the vndersetters thereof were of the base it selfe.
verse_text: Nam et humeruli illi quatuor per singulos angulos basis unius, ex ipsa basi fusiles et conjuncti erant.

text: But they that shal be counted worthie of that world and the resurrection from the dead, neither marrie, nor take wiues;
verse_text: but they which shalbe made worthy to enioye that worlde and the resurreccion from deeth nether mary wyves nether are maryed

text: And foure vndersetters were vpon the foure corners of one base: and the vndersetters thereof were of the base it selfe.
verse_text: And the four undersetters that were at every corner of each base, were of the base itself cast and joined together.

text: But they that shal be counted worthie of that world and the resurrection from the dead, neither marrie, nor take wiues;
verse_text: but thei that schulen be had worthi of that world, and of the risyng ayen fro deeth, nethir ben wedded,

text: For it is easier for a camel to passe through the eye of a nedle, then for a rich man to enter into the Kingdom of God.
verse_text: for it is liyter a camel to passe thorou a nedlis iye, than a riche man to entre in to the kyngdom of God.

text: Propter hoc haec dicit Dominus Deus: Ecce servi mei comedent, et vos esurietis; ecce servi mei bibent, et vos sitietis;
verse_text: Therefore thus saith the Lord God: Behold my servants shall eat, and you shall be hungry: behold my servants shall drink, and you shall be thirsty.

text: Their empire also is lost from Heshbon vnto Dibon, and wee haue destroyed them vnto Nophah, which reacheth vnto Medeba.
verse_text: Jugum ipsorum disperiit ad Hesebon usque Dibon: lassi pervenerunt in Nophe, et usque Medaba.

text: But exhort one another dayly, while it is called to day, lest any of you be hardened through the deceitfulnes of sinne.
verse_text: sed adhortamini vosmetipsos per singulos dies, donec hodie cognominatur, ut non obduretur quis ex vobis fallacia peccati.

text: But beloued, we haue perswaded our selues better things of you, and such as accompany saluation, though we thus speake.
verse_text: Confidimus autem de vobis dilectissimi meliora, et viciniora saluti: tametsi ita loquimur.

text: But they that shal be counted worthie of that world and the resurrection from the dead, neither marrie, nor take wiues;
verse_text: illi vero qui digni habebuntur saeculo illo, et resurrectione ex mortuis, neque nubent, neque ducent uxores:

text: But beloued, we haue perswaded our selues better things of you, and such as accompany saluation, though we thus speake.
verse_text: Neverthelesse deare frendes we trust to se better of you and thynges which accompany saluacion though we thus speake.

text: Therfor go ye, and teche alle folkis, baptisynge hem in the name of the Fadir, and of the Sone, and of the Hooli Goost;
verse_text: Go therfore and teache all nacions baptysinge them in the name of the father and the sonne and the holy goost:

text: For there are three, which beare recorde in heauen, the Father, the Worde, and the holy Ghost: and these three are one.
verse_text: (For ther are thre which beare recorde in heuen the father the worde and the wholy goost. And these thre are one)

text: In the seuenth day also ye shall offer seuen bullocks, two rammes and fourteene lambes of a yeere olde without blemish,
verse_text: The seventh day you shall offer seven calves and two rams, and fourteen lambs of a year old, without blemish:

text: And vpon the forefront of the entry of the gate vnto the forefront of the porch of the gate within were fiftie cubites.
verse_text: Et ante faciem portae quae pertingebat usque ad faciem vestibuli portae interioris, quinquaginta cubitos.

text: That as sinne reigned to death; so also grace may reigne by iustice to life euerlasting, through IESVS Christ our Lord.
verse_text: ut sicut regnavit peccatum in mortem: ita et gratia regnet per justitiam in vitam aeternam, per Jesum Christum Dominum nostrum.

text: And their meat offring of fine floure mingled with oyle, three tenth deales vnto a bullocke, two tenth deales to a ram,
verse_text: and in the sacrifices of tho ye schulen offre thre tenthe partis of flour spreynt togidere with oile, bi ech calf, twei tenthe partis bi rammes,

text: For neither haue we been, at any time in the word of adulation, as you know; nor in occasion of auarice, God is witnes:
verse_text: Neither yet did we euer vse flattering wordes, as ye knowe, nor coloured couetousnes, God is recorde.

text: And they cried with a loud voice, saying, Saluation commeth of our God, that sitteth vpon the throne, and of the Lambe.
verse_text: and cryed with a lowde voyce sayinge: salvacion be asscribed to him that syttith apon the seate of oure god and vnto the lambe.

text: In the seuenth day also ye shall offer seuen bullocks, two rammes and fourteene lambes of a yeere olde without blemish,
verse_text: And on the seuenth day, seuen bullockes, two rammes, and fourteene lambes of the first yeere without blemish.

text: Hauing made knowen vnto vs the mysterie of his will, according to his good pleasure, which he had purposed in himselfe,
verse_text: ut notum faceret nobis sacramentum voluntatis suae, secundum beneplacitum ejus, quod proposuit in eo,

text: Euery bed whereon he lyeth that hath the issue, shall be vncleane, and euery thing whereon he sitteth, shalbe vncleane.
verse_text: Every bed on which he sleepeth, shall be unclean, and every place on which he sitteth.

text: And I say vnto you, Aske, and it shall be giuen you: seeke, and yee shall finde: knocke, and it shalbe opened vnto you.
verse_text: And Y seie to you, axe ye, and it schal be youun to you; seke ye, and ye schulen fynde; knocke ye, and it schal be openyd to you.

text: For there are three, which beare recorde in heauen, the Father, the Worde, and the holy Ghost: and these three are one.
verse_text: Quoniam tres sunt, qui testimonium dant in caelo: Pater, Verbum, et Spiritus Sanctus: et hi tres unum sunt.

text: For whosoeuer will saue his life, shall lose it: and whosoeuer shall lose his life for my sake, the same shall saue it.
verse_text: Whosoever will save his lyfe shall lose it. And who soever shall lose his lyfe for my sake the same shall save it.

text: For vnto this are you called: because Christ also suffered for vs leauing you an example that you may follow his steps.
verse_text: In hoc enim vocati estis: quia et Christus passus est pro nobis, vobis relinquens exemplum ut sequamini vestigia ejus:

text: Knowing this first, that in the last daies shal come mockers in deceit, walking according to their owne concupiscences,
verse_text: This fyrst vnderstode that ther shall come in the last dayes mockers which will walke after their awne lustes

text: And whatsoeuer soule it bee that doeth any worke in that same day, the same soule will I destroy from among his people.
verse_text: and Y schal do a way fro his puple that man that doith eny thing of werk in that dai;

text: Et dissipabunt muros Tyri, et destruent turres ejus: et radam pulverem ejus de ea, et dabo eam in limpidissimam petram.
verse_text: And they shall break down the walls of Tyre, and destroy the towers thereof: and I will scrape her dust from her, and make her like a smooth rock.

text: And I say vnto you, Aske, and it shall be giuen you: seeke, and yee shall finde: knocke, and it shalbe opened vnto you.
verse_text: And I saye vnto you: axe and it shalbe geven you. Seke and ye shall fynde. knocke and it shalbe opened vnto you.

text: Of his owne will begate hee vs, with the word of Trueth, that wee should bee a kinde of first fruites of his creatures.
verse_text: Voluntarie enim genuit nos verbo veritatis, ut simus initium aliquod creaturae ejus.

text: And I say vnto you, Aske, and it shall be giuen you: seeke, and yee shall finde: knocke, and it shalbe opened vnto you.
verse_text: Et ego dico vobis: Petite, et dabitur vobis; quaerite, et invenietis; pulsate, et aperietur vobis.

text: And he shall prepare a meate offring of an Ephah for a bullocke, an Ephah for a ramme, and an Hin of oyle for an Ephah.
verse_text: And he shall offer the sacrifice of an ephi for every calf, and an ephi for every ram: and a hin of oil for every ephi.

text: Litle children, ye are of God, and haue ouercome them: for greater is he that is in you, then he that is in this world.
verse_text: Vos ex Deo estis filioli, et vicistis eum, quoniam major est qui in vobis est, quam qui in mundo.

text: Whereof I am made a minister by the gift of the grace of God giuen vnto me through the effectuall working of his power.
verse_text: cujus factus sum minister secundum donum gratiae Dei, quae data est mihi secundum operationem virtutis ejus.

text: And he shall prepare a meate offring of an Ephah for a bullocke, an Ephah for a ramme, and an Hin of oyle for an Ephah.
verse_text: Et sacrificium ephi per vitulum, et ephi per arietem faciet, et olei hin per singula ephi.

text: Duas quoque pingues vaccas, et quatuor arietes, occidi fecit, et parari epulas omnibus vicinis suis, cunctisque amicis.
verse_text: He caused also two fat kine, and four wethers to be killed, and a banquet to be prepared for all his neighbours, and all his friends.

text: In the second yere of Pekah the sonne of Remaliah King of Israel, began Iotham sonne of Vzziah King of Iudah to reigne.
verse_text: In the second year of Phacee the son of Romelia king of Israel reigned Joatham son of Ozias king of Juda.

text: sed caput Syriae Damascus, et caput Damasci Rasin; et adhuc sexaginta et quinque anni, et desinet Ephraim esse populus;
verse_text: But the head of Syria is Damascus, and the head of Damascus is Basin: and within threescore and five years, Ephraim shall cease to be a people:

text: And the sonnes of Midian were Ephah, and Ephar, and Henoch, and Abida, and Eldaah: All these are the sonnes of Keturah.
verse_text: And the sons of Madian: Epha, and Epher, and Henoch, and Abida, and Eldaa. All these are the sons of Cetura.

text: My soule longeth, yea, and fainteth for the courtes of the Lord: for mine heart and my flesh reioyce in the liuing God.
verse_text: Benedixisti, Domine, terram tuam; avertisti captivitatem Jacob.

text: This only would I learne of you, Receiued ye the Spirit by the workes of the Lawe, or by the hearing of faith preached?
verse_text: Hoc solum a vobis volo discere: ex operibus legis Spiritum accepistis, an ex auditu fidei?

text: For he hath made him to be sinne for vs, which knewe no sinne, that we should be made the righteousnesse of God in him.
verse_text: Eum, qui non noverat peccatum, pro nobis peccatum fecit, ut nos efficeremur justitia Dei in ipso.

text: But thou, continue in those things which thou hast learned, & are committed to thee: knowing of whom thou hast learned;
verse_text: Tu vero permane in iis quae didicisti, et credita sunt tibi: sciens a quo didiceris:

text: Now the God of patience and consolation giue you that ye be like minded one towards another, according to Christ Iesus,
verse_text: Deus autem patientiae et solatii det vobis idipsum sapere in alterutrum secundum Jesum Christum:

text: Et factum est, ut viderunt qui interpellabant gloriam ejus, quae praedicabatur, et opertum eum purpura, fugerunt omnes:
verse_text: So when his accusers saw his glory proclaimed, and him clothed with purple, they all fled away.

text: What I tell you in darkenesse, that speake yee in light: and what yee heare in the eare, that preach yee on the houses.
verse_text: What I tell you in dercknes that speake ye in lyght. And what ye heare in the eare that preache the on the housse toppes.

text: And thou shalt set the Altar of the burnt offering, before the doore of the Tabernacle of the Tent of the Congregation.
verse_text: and bifor it the auter of brent sacrifice,

text: So when much time was spent, and sayling was now ieopardous, because also the Fast was nowe passed, Paul exhorted them,
verse_text: When moche tyme was spent and saylinge was now ieoperdeous because also that we had overlonge fasted Paul put them in remembraunce

text: I exhorte therfore that above all thynges prayers supplicacions intercessions and gevynge of thankes behad for all men:
verse_text: I Exhort therefore, that first of all supplications, prayers, intercessions, and giuing of thanks be made for all men,

text: They haue said, Come and let vs cut them off from being a nation: and let the name of Israel be no more in remembrance.
verse_text: Etenim passer invenit sibi domum, et turtur nidum sibi, ubi ponat pullos suos: altaria tua, Domine virtutum, rex meus, et Deus meus.

text: Then shall the iust men shine as ye sunne in the kingdome of their Father. Hee that hath eares to heare, let him heare.
verse_text: Tunc justi fulgebunt sicut sol in regno Patris eorum. Qui habet aures audiendi, audiat.

text: And their meat offring of fine floure mingled with oyle, three tenth deales vnto a bullocke, two tenth deales to a ram,
verse_text: atque in sacrificiis eorum, similae oleo conspersae tres decimas per singulos vitulos, per arietes duas,

text: Then when Festus had spoken with the Council, hee answered, Hast thou appealed vnto Caesar? vnto Caesar shalt thou goe.
verse_text: Tunc Festus cum concilio locutus, respondit: Caesarem appellasti? ad Caesarem ibis.

text: In the seuenth day also ye shall offer seuen bullocks, two rammes and fourteene lambes of a yeere olde without blemish,
verse_text: In the seuenthe dai ye schulen offre seuene calues, twei rammes, fourtene lambren of o yeer with out wem.

text: Verely I say vnto you, all sinnes shalbe forgiuen vnto the children of men, and blasphemies, wherewith they blaspheme:
verse_text: Treuli Y seie to you, that alle synnes and blasfemyes, bi whiche thei han blasfemed, schulen be foryouun to the sones of men.

text: But I say vnto you, Resist not euill: but whosoeuer shall smite thee on thy right cheeke, turne to him the other also.
verse_text: But I saye to you that ye resist not wronge. But whosoever geve the a blowe on thy right cheke tourne to him the other.

text: And declared mightily to be the Sonne of God, touching the Spirit of sanctification by the resurrection from the dead)
verse_text: qui praedestinatus est Filius Dei in virtute secundum spiritum sanctificationis ex resurrectione mortuorum Jesu Christi Domini nostri:

text: And he said: Then, father, I beseech thee that thou wouldest send him vnto my fathers house, for I haue fiue brethren,
verse_text: And he seide, Thanne Y preie thee, fadir, that thou sende hym in to the hous of my fadir.

text: For they be thy people, and thine inheritance, which thou broughtest out of Egypt from the middes of the yron fornace.
verse_text: Populus enim tuus est, et haereditas tua, quos eduxisti de terra AEgypti, de medio fornacis ferreae.

text: He that spared not also his owne Sonne, but for vs al deliuered him; how hath he not also with him giuen vs al things?
verse_text: Qui etiam proprio Filio suo non pepercit, sed pro nobis omnibus tradidit illum: quomodo non etiam cum illo omnia nobis donavit?

text: But I say vnto you, Resist not euill: but whosoeuer shall smite thee on thy right cheeke, turne to him the other also.
verse_text: But Y seie to you, that ye ayenstonde not an yuel man; but if ony smyte thee in the riyt cheke, schewe to him also the tothir;

text: That which goeth into the mouth, defileth not the man, but that which commeth out of the mouth, that defileth the man.
verse_text: That thing that entrith in to the mouth, defoulith not a man; but that thing that cometh out of the mouth, defoulith a man.

text: going therfore teach ye al Nations: BAPTIZING THEM IN THE NAME OF THE FATHER, AND OF THE SONNE, AND OF THE HOLY GHOST,
verse_text: Go therfore and teache all nacions baptysinge them in the name of the father and the sonne and the holy goost:

text: going therfore teach ye al Nations: BAPTIZING THEM IN THE NAME OF THE FATHER, AND OF THE SONNE, AND OF THE HOLY GHOST,
verse_text: Go therefore, and teach all nations, baptizing them in the Name of the Father, and the Sonne, and the holy Ghost,

text: Keepe thou therefore the commandements, and the ordinances, and the lawes, which I commaund thee this day to doe them.
verse_text: Keep therefore the precepts and ceremonies and judgments, which I command thee this day to do.

text: Keepe thou therefore the commandements, and the ordinances, and the lawes, which I commaund thee this day to doe them.
verse_text: Custodi ergo praecepta et caeremonias atque judicia, quae ego mando tibi hodie ut facias.

text: going therfore teach ye al Nations: BAPTIZING THEM IN THE NAME OF THE FATHER, AND OF THE SONNE, AND OF THE HOLY GHOST,
verse_text: Therfor go ye, and teche alle folkis, baptisynge hem in the name of the Fadir, and of the Sone, and of the Hooli Goost;

text: Who hath predestinate vs, to be adopted through Iesus Christ in him selfe, according to the good pleasure of his will,
verse_text: And ordeyned vs before thorow Iesus Christ to be heyres vnto him silfe accordinge to the pleasure of his will

text: Memento horum Jacob, et Israel, quoniam servus meus es tu. Formavi te; servus meus es tu, Israel, ne obliviscaris mei.
verse_text: Remember these things, O Jacob, and Israel, for thou art my servant. I have formed thee, thou art my servant, O Israel, forget me not.

text: And behold men carying in a bed a man that had the palsey: and they sought to bring him in, and to lay him before him.
verse_text: And lo! men beren in a bed a man that was sijk in the palsye, and thei souyten to bere hym in, and sette bifor hym.

text: I Exhort therefore, that first of all supplications, prayers, intercessions, and giuing of thanks be made for all men,
verse_text: Obsecro igitur primum omnium fieri obsecrationes, orationes, postulationes, gratiarum actiones, pro omnibus hominibus:

text: If I through Beelzebub cast out deuils, by whome doe your children cast them out? Therefore shall they be your iudges.
verse_text: Si autem ego in Beelzebub ejicio daemonia: filii vestri in quo ejiciunt? ideo ipsi judices vestri erunt.

text: Et cum egrederetur de templo, ait illi unus ex discipulis suis: Magister, aspice quales lapides, et quales structurae.
verse_text: And as he went out of the temple one of his disciples sayde vnto him: Master se what stones and what byldynges are here.

text: Si autem aversum fuerit cor tuum, et audire nolueris, atque errore deceptus adoraveris deos alienos, et servieris eis:
verse_text: But if thy heart be turned away, so that thou wilt not hear, and being deceived with error thou adore strange gods, and serve them:

text: A Psalme of David. The Lord said vnto my Lord, Sit thou at my right hand, vntill I make thine enemies thy footestoole.
verse_text: Alleluja. Confitebor tibi, Domine, in toto corde meo, in consilio justorum, et congregatione.

text: For if ye liue after the flesh, ye shall die: but if yee mortifie the deedes of the body by the Spirit, ye shall liue.
verse_text: For if ye live after the flesshe ye must dye. But yf ye mortifie the dedes of the body by the helpe of the sprite ye shall lyve.

text: Yet in the three and twentieth yeere of King Iehoash the Priestes had not mended that which was decayed in the Temple.
verse_text: Igitur usque ad vigesimum tertium annum regis Joas, non instauraverunt sacerdotes sartatecta templi.

text: And the asshe pannes, and the basens, and all that was of gold, and that was of siluer, tooke the chiefe steward away,
verse_text: Necnon et thuribula, et phialas: quae aurea, aurea, et quae argentea, argentea tulit princeps militiae,

text: Quatuor ergo viri erant leprosi juxta introitum portae: qui dixerunt ad invicem: Quid hic esse volumus donec moriamur?
verse_text: Now there were four lepers, at the entering in of the gate: and they said one to another: What mean we to stay here till we die?

text: Propter hoc dabit Dominus ipse vobis signum: ecce virgo concipiet, et pariet filium, et vocabitur nomen ejus Emmanuel.
verse_text: Therefore the Lord himself shall give you a sign. Behold a virgin shall conceive, and bear a son, and his name shall be called Emmanuel.

text: Verely I say vnto you, all sinnes shalbe forgiuen vnto the children of men, and blasphemies, wherewith they blaspheme:
verse_text: Verely I saye vnto you all synnes shalbe forgeven vnto mens chyldren and blasphemy wherwith they blaspheme.

text: But I say vnto you, Resist not euill: but whosoeuer shall smite thee on thy right cheeke, turne to him the other also.
verse_text: Ego autem dico vobis, non resistere malo: sed si quis te percusserit in dexteram maxillam tuam, praebe illi et alteram:

text: Hide not thy face from me in the time of my trouble: incline thine eares vnto me: when I call, make haste to heare me.
verse_text: Benedic, anima mea, Domino, et noli oblivisci omnes retributiones ejus.

text: going therfore teach ye al Nations: BAPTIZING THEM IN THE NAME OF THE FATHER, AND OF THE SONNE, AND OF THE HOLY GHOST,
verse_text: euntes ergo docete omnes gentes: baptizantes eos in nomine Patris, et Filii, et Spiritus Sancti:

text: God is greatly to be feared in the assembly of the Saints: and to bee had in reuerence of all them that are about him.
verse_text: Quia defecimus in ira tua, et in furore tuo turbati sumus.

text: Tu, Domine, elegisti domum istam ad invocandum nomen tuum in ea, ut esset domus orationis et obsecrationis populo tuo:
verse_text: Thou, O Lord, hast chosen this house for thy name to be called upon therein, that it might be a house of prayer and supplication for thy people.

text: Who hath predestinate vs, to be adopted through Iesus Christ in him selfe, according to the good pleasure of his will,
verse_text: Qui praedestinavit nos in adoptionem filiorum per Jesum Christum in ipsum: secundum propositum voluntatis suae,

text: For who in the heauen can be compared vnto the Lord? who among the sonnes of the mightie can be likened vnto the Lord?
verse_text: Mane sicut herba transeat; mane floreat, et transeat; vespere decidat, induret, et arescat.

text: And because ye are sonnes, God hath sent foorth the Spirit of his Sonne into your heartes, which crieth, Abba, Father.
verse_text: Quoniam autem estis filii, misit Deus Spiritum Filii sui in corda vestra, clamantem: Abba, Pater.

text: According to thy Name, O God, so is thy praise vnto the endes of the earth: thy right hand is full of righteousnesse.
verse_text: et vivet adhuc in finem.

text: According to thy Name, O God, so is thy praise vnto the endes of the earth: thy right hand is full of righteousnesse.
verse_text: and shal liue yet vnto the end.

text: qui eduxit ad dexteram Moysen, brachio majestatis suae; qui scidit aquas ante eos, ut faceret sibi nomen sempiternum;
verse_text: He that brought out Moses by the right hand, by the arm of his majesty: that divided the waters before them, to make himself an everlasting name.

text: Thou shalt not pity him, but shalt require life for life, eye for eye, tooth for tooth, hand for hand, foot for foot.
verse_text: Thou schalt not haue mercy on hym, but thou schalt axe lijf for lijf, iye for iye, tooth for tooth, hond for hond, foot for foot.

text: And the fourth Angel poured out his vial vpon the sunne, and it was giuen vnto him to afflict men with heat and fire:
verse_text: Et quartus angelus effudit phialam suam in solem, et datum est illi aestu affligere homines, et igni:

text: And I will destroy your land, and your enemies shall be astonished at it, when they shall be the inhabitants thereof.
verse_text: I will also bring the land vnto a wildernes, and your enemies, which dwell therein, shalbe astonished thereat.

text: And they reasoned within themselues, saying, If we shall say, From heauen, he will say, Why then beleeued ye him not?
verse_text: At illi cogitabant intra se, dicentes: Quia si dixerimus: De caelo, dicet: Quare ergo non credidistis illi?

text: On the East, three gates: and on the North, three gates: and on the South, three gates: and on the West, three gates.
verse_text: ab oriente portae tres, et ab aquilone portae tres, et ab austro portae tres, et ab occasu portae tres.

text: Iesus sayd to him, Thou shalt loue the Lord thy God with all thine heart, with all thy soule, and with all thy minde.
verse_text: Ait illi Jesus: Diliges Dominum Deum tuum ex toto corde tuo, et in tota anima tua, et in tota mente tua.

text: For it is not a good tree that bringeth foorth euill fruite: neither an euill tree, that bringeth foorth good fruite.
verse_text: Non est enim arbor bona, quae facit fructus malos: neque arbor mala, faciens fructum bonum.

text: For it is not a good tree that bringeth foorth euill fruite: neither an euill tree, that bringeth foorth good fruite.
verse_text: It is not a good tree, that makith yuel fruytis, nether an yuel tree, that makith good fruytis;

text: Iesus sayd to him, Thou shalt loue the Lord thy God with all thine heart, with all thy soule, and with all thy minde.
verse_text: Iesus sayde vnto him: love the Lorde thy God with all thine herte with all thy soule and with all thy mynde.

text: Not vnto vs, O Lord, not vnto vs, but vnto thy Name giue the glorie, for thy louing mercie and for thy truethes sake.
verse_text: Alleluja. Credidi, propter quod locutus sum; ego autem humiliatus sum nimis.

text: For it is not a good tree that bringeth foorth euill fruite: neither an euill tree, that bringeth foorth good fruite.
verse_text: It is not a good tree that bringeth forthe evyll frute: nether is that an evyll tree that bringeth forthe good frute.

text: Deo autem gratias, qui semper triumphat nos in Christo Jesu, et odorem notitiae suae manifestat per nos in omni loco:
verse_text: Thankes be vnto God which alwayes geveth vs the victorie in Christ and openeth the saver of his knowledge by vs in every place.

text: So they died of this plague fourtene thousande and seuen hundreth, beside them that dyed in the conspiracie of Korah.
verse_text: Sotheli thei that weren smytun weren fourtene thousynde of men and seuene hundrid, with outen hem that perischiden in the discencioun of Chore.

text: But nowe is the righteousnesse, of God made manifest without the Lawe, hauing witnes of the Lawe and of the Prophets,
verse_text: Nunc autem sine lege justitia Dei manifestata est: testificata a lege et prophetis.

text: Returne thou therefore, and obey the voyce of the Lord, and do all his commandements, which I commaund thee this day.
verse_text: Sotheli thou schalt turne ayen, and schalt here the vois of thi Lord God, and schalt do alle the heestis whiche Y comaunde to thee to dai;

text: Thus Moses spake in the audience of all the congregation of Israel the wordes of this song, vntill he had ended them.
verse_text: Moses therefore spoke, in the hearing of the whole assembly of Israel, the words of this canticle, and finished it even to the end,

text: And they thought with themselues, saying, If we shall say, From heauen, he will say, Why then did ye not beleeue him?
verse_text: And thei thouyten with ynne hem silf, seiynge, If we seien of heuene, he schal seie to vs, Whi thanne bileuen ye not to him;

text: Prayse the Lord, ye his Angels, that excell in strength, that doe his commandement in obeying the voyce of his worde.
verse_text: Posuisti tenebras, et facta est nox; in ipsa pertransibunt omnes bestiae silvae:

text: And I could not speake vnto you, brethren, as vnto spirituall men, but as vnto carnall, euen as vnto babes in Christ.
verse_text: Et ego, fratres, non potui vobis loqui quasi spiritualibus, sed quasi carnalibus. Tamquam parvulis in Christo,

text: that your faith might not be in the wisedom of men, but in the power of God. But we speake wisedom among the perfect.
verse_text: ut fides vestra non sit in sapientia hominum, sed in virtute Dei.

text: So they died of this plague fourtene thousande and seuen hundreth, beside them that dyed in the conspiracie of Korah.
verse_text: Fuerunt autem qui percussi sunt, quatuordecim millia hominum, et septingenti, absque his qui perierant in seditione Core.

text: And an hee goate for a sinne offring, beside the continuall burnt offring, his meate offering and his drinke offring.
verse_text: And ye schulen offre a buc of geet for synne, with out euerlastynge brent sacrifice, and with out the sacrifice and moiste offryng therof.

text: And Peter going downe to the men, said: Behold I am he whom you seeke; what is the cause, for the which you are come?
verse_text: Peter went doune to the men which were sent vnto him from Cornelius and sayde Beholde I am he whom ye seke what is the cause wherfore ye are come?

text: For in Iesus Christ neither circumcision auaileth any thing, neither vncircumcision, but faith which worketh by loue.
verse_text: Nam in Christo Jesu neque circumcisio aliquid valet, neque praeputium: sed fides, quae per caritatem operatur.

text: Perceiue ye not yet, that whatsoeuer entreth into the mouth, goeth into the bellie, and is cast out into the draught?
verse_text: Non intelligitis quia omne quod in os intrat, in ventrem vadit, et in secessum emittitur?

text: And he commanded the chariot to stay: and both went downe into the water, Philip and the Eunuch, and he baptized him.
verse_text: Et jussit stare currum: et descenderunt uterque in aquam, Philippus et eunuchus, et baptizavit eum.

text: Hic est discipulus ille qui testimonium perhibet de his, et scripsit haec: et scimus quia verum est testimonium ejus.
verse_text: The same disciple is he which testifieth of these thinges and wrote these thinges. And we knowe that his testimony is true.

text: And he commanded the chariot to stay: and both went downe into the water, Philip and the Eunuch, and he baptized him.
verse_text: And he commaunded the charet to stonde still. And they went doune bothe into the water: bothe Philip and also the chamberlayne and he baptised him.

text: Perceiue ye not yet, that whatsoeuer entreth into the mouth, goeth into the bellie, and is cast out into the draught?
verse_text: Vndurstonden ye not, that al thing that entrith in to the mouth, goith in to the wombe, and is sent out in to the goyng awei?

text: But the Iewes that were incredulous, stirred vp and incensed the hartes of the Gentils to anger against the Brethren.
verse_text: But the unbelevinge Iewes steryd vp and vnquyeted the myndes of the Gentyls agaynste the brethren.

verse_id: Numbers 29.16 (Douay-Rheims); Numbers 29.25 (Douay-Rheims); Numbers 29.28 (Douay-Rheims); Numbers 29.31 (Douay-Rheims); Numbers 29.34 (Douay-Rheims); Numbers 29.38 (Douay-Rheims)
text: And an hee goate for a sinne offring, beside the continuall burnt offring, his meate offering and his drinke offring.
verse_text: And a buck goat for sin, besides the perpetual holocaust, and the sacrifice and the libation thereof.

text: If I had not come and spoken vnto them, they shoulde not haue had sinne: but nowe haue they no cloke for their sinne.
verse_text: If Y hadde not comun, and hadde not spokun to hem, thei schulden not haue synne; but now thei haue noon excusacioun of her synne.

text: The heauens are thine, the earth also is thine: thou hast layde the foundation of the world, and all that therein is.
verse_text: Quis novit potestatem irae tuae, et prae timore tuo iram tuam

text: But if a man find a damsel that is betrothed, in the field, and taking hold of her, lie with her, he alone shall die:
verse_text: Forsothe if a man fyndith in the feeld a damysel, which is spousid, and he takith, and doith letcherie with hir, he aloone schal die;

text: For in Iesus Christ neither circumcision auaileth any thing, neither vncircumcision, but faith which worketh by loue.
verse_text: For in Iesu Christ nether is circumcision enythinge worth nether yet vncircomcision but faith which by love is mighty in operacion.

text: Let no man therfore iudge you in meat or in drinke, or in part of a festiual day, or of the New-moon, or of Sabboths:
verse_text: Nemo ergo vos judicet in cibo, aut in potu, aut in parte diei festi, aut neomeniae, aut sabbatorum:

text: and to you that are vexed, rest with vs in the reuelation of our Lord IESVS from Heauen with the Angels of his power,
verse_text: et vobis, qui tribulamini, requiem nobiscum in revelatione Domini Jesu de caelo cum angelis virtutis ejus,

text: And an hee goate for a sinne offring, beside the continuall burnt offring, his meate offering and his drinke offring.
verse_text: And one goat for a sinne offring, beside the continuall burnt offering, his meate offering, and his drinke offring.

text: Let no man therfore iudge you in meat or in drinke, or in part of a festiual day, or of the New-moon, or of Sabboths:
verse_text: Let noman therfore trouble youre conscieces aboute meate and drynke or for a pece of an holydaye as the holydaye of the newe mone or of the sabboth dayes

text: And an hee goate for a sinne offring, beside the continuall burnt offring, his meate offering and his drinke offring.
verse_text: et hircum pro peccato, absque holocausto sempiterno, sacrificioque ejus et libamine.

text: Whom I woulde haue reteined with mee, that in thy steade he might haue ministred vnto me in the bondes of the Gospel.
verse_text: quem ego volueram mecum detinere, ut pro te mihi ministraret in vinculis Evangelii:

text: Ye are witnesses, and God also, how holily, and iustly, and vnblameably we behaued our selues among you that beleeue.
verse_text: Vos testes estis, et Deus, quam sancte, et juste, et sine querela, vobis, qui credidistis, fuimus:

text: And Iosias begate Iakim. And Iakim begate Iechonias and his brethren about the time they were caried away to Babylon.
verse_text: Iosias begat Iechonias and his brethren aboute the tyme they were caryed awaye to Babylon.

text: Wherein yee reioyce, though nowe for a season (if neede require) yee are in heauinesse, through manifolde tentations,
verse_text: In quo exsultabis, modicum nunc si oportet contristari in variis tentationibus:

text: For there be three which giue testimonie in heauen, the Father, the Word, and the Holy Ghost. And these three be one.
verse_text: (For ther are thre which beare recorde in heuen the father the worde and the wholy goost. And these thre are one)

text: If any man come to you, and bring not this doctrine, receiue him not into the house, nor say, God saue you, vnto him.
verse_text: Si quis venit ad vos, et hanc doctrinam non affert, nolite recipere eum in domum, nec Ave ei dixeritis.

text: For there be three which giue testimonie in heauen, the Father, the Word, and the Holy Ghost. And these three be one.
verse_text: Quoniam tres sunt, qui testimonium dant in caelo: Pater, Verbum, et Spiritus Sanctus: et hi tres unum sunt.

text: And they reasoned with themselues, saying, If wee shall say, From heauen, he will say, Why then beleeued yee him not?
verse_text: And thei thouyten with ynne hem silf, seiynge, For if we seien, Of heuene, he schal seie, Whi thanne bileuen ye not to hym?

text: The voyce of the Lord is vpon the waters: the God of glorie maketh it to thunder: the Lord is vpon the great waters.
verse_text: Domine Deus meus, clamavi ad te, et sanasti me.

text: Let them consume like a snayle that melteth, and like the vntimely fruite of a woman, that hath not seene the sunne.
verse_text: Ecce loquentur in ore suo, et gladius in labiis eorum: quoniam quis audivit?

text: Ye shall do no maner worke therefore: this shalbe a law for euer in your generations, throughout all your dwellings.
verse_text: therfor ye schulen not do ony thing of werk in that dai; it schal be a lawful thing euerlastynge to you in alle youre generaciouns and abitaciouns;

text: And they asked him, and said to him: Why then doest thou baptize, if thou be not Christ, nor Elias, nor the Prophet?
verse_text: Et interrogaverunt eum, et dixerunt ei: Quid ergo baptizas, si tu non es Christus, neque Elias, neque propheta?

text: But he that doth veritie, commeth to the light, that his workes may be made manifest, because they were done in God.
verse_text: qui autem facit veritatem, venit ad lucem, ut manifestentur opera ejus, quia in Deo sunt facta.

text: But if I say thus vnto the boy, Behold, the arrowes are beyonde thee, goe thy way: for the Lord hath sent thee away.
verse_text: If I shall say to the boy: Behold the arrows are on this side of thee, take them up: come thou to me, because, there is peace to thee, and there is no evil, as the Lord liveth. But if I shall speak thus to the boy: Behold the arrows are beyond thee: go in peace, for the Lord hath sent thee away.

text: Let your light so shine before men, that they may see your good workes, and glorifie your Father which is in heauen.
verse_text: So schyne youre liyt befor men, that thei se youre goode werkis, and glorifie youre fadir that is in heuenes.

text: And the second day ye shall offer twelue yong bullockes, two rams, fourteene lambes of a yeere olde without blemish,
verse_text: And on the second day ye shal offer twelue yong bullocks, two rammes, foureteene lambes of the first yeere without spot.

text: That I may see the felicitie of thy chosen, and reioyce in the ioy of thy people, and glorie with thine inheritance.
verse_text: Esurientes et sitientes, anima eorum in ipsis defecit.

text: And that no man might buy or sell, saue hee that had the marke, or the name of the beast, or the number of his name.
verse_text: et nequis possit emere, aut vendere, nisi qui habet caracterem, aut nomen bestiae, aut numerum nominis ejus.

text: My soule longeth, yea euen fainteth for the courts of the Lord: my heart and my flesh cryeth out for the liuing God.
verse_text: Benedixisti, Domine, terram tuam; avertisti captivitatem Jacob.

text: Giuing thankes vnto the Father, which hath made vs meete to be partakers of the inheritance of the Saintes in light,
verse_text: gratias agentes Deo Patri, qui dignos nos fecit in partem sortis sanctorum in lumine:

text: Which being past feeling, haue giuen themselues vnto wantonnesse, to woorke all vncleannesse, euen with griedinesse.
verse_text: which beynge past repentaunce have geven them selves vnto wantannes to worke all manner of vnclennes even with gredynes.

text: and leauing the citie of Nazareth, came and dwelt in Capharnaum a sea towne, in the borders of Zabulon of Nephthali;
verse_text: et, relicta civitate Nazareth, venit, et habitavit in Capharnaum maritima, in finibus Zabulon et Nephthalim:

text: So let your light shine before men, that they may see your good workes, and glorifie your Father which is in Heauen.
verse_text: Nolite putare quoniam veni solvere legem aut prophetas: non veni solvere, sed adimplere.

text: But if thy meate offring be an oblation of the frying pan, it shall be of fine flowre vnleauened, mingled with oyle.
verse_text: if thin offryng is of a friyng panne, of wheete flour spreynd with oile and without sour dow,

text: For if the inheritance be of the Lawe, it is no more by the promise, but God gaue it freely vnto Abraham by promise.
verse_text: Nam si ex lege haereditas, jam non ex promissione. Abrahae autem per repromissionem donavit Deus.

text: For if the inheritance be of the Lawe, it is no more by the promise, but God gaue it freely vnto Abraham by promise.

text: Then the foure and twentie Elders, which sate before God on their seates, fell vpon their faces, and worshipped God,

text: Et dixit mihi: Factum est: ego sum alpha et omega, initium et finis. Ego sitienti dabo de fonte aquae vitae, gratis.

text: Which is the earnest of our inheritance, for the redemption of that libertie purchased vnto the prayse of his glory.

text: Paravit Dominus brachium sanctum suum in oculis omnium gentium; et videbunt omnes fines terrae salutare Dei nostri.

text: Nowe yee take this also away from me: if death take him, then yee shall bring my graye head in sorowe to the graue.
