text: PAVL an Apostle of IESVS Christ by the wil of God, according to the promise of the life which is in Christ IESVS:
verse_text: Paulus Apostolus Jesu Christi per voluntatem Dei, secundum promissionem vitae, quae est in Christo Jesu,

text: And after the yeere was gone about, Ben-hadad nombred the Aramites, and went vp to Aphek to fight against Israel.
verse_text: Igitur postquam annus transierat, recensuit Benadad Syros, et ascendit in Aphec ut pugnaret contra Israel.

text: Then he founde another man, and sayde, Smite mee, I pray thee. And the man smote him, and in smiting wounded him.
verse_text: Sed alterum inveniens virum, dixit ad eum: Percute me. Qui percussit eum, et vulneravit.

text: But I haue prayed for thee, that thy faith faile not: therefore when thou art conuerted, strengthen thy brethren.
verse_text: that thi feith faile not; and thou sum tyme conuertid, conferme thi britheren.

text: And cried with a loude voyce, as when a lyon roareth: and when he had cried, seuen thunders vttered their voyces.
verse_text: et clamavit voce magna, quemadmodum cum leo rugit. Et cum clamasset, locuta sunt septem tonitrua voces suas.

text: Similiter autem et Judas ea quae deciderant per bellum quod nobis acciderat, congregavit omnia, et sunt apud nos.
verse_text: And in like manner Judas also gathered together all such things as were lost by the war we had, and they are in our possession.

text: Propterea dixi: Recedite a me: amare flebo; nolite incumbere ut consolemini me super vastitate filiae populi mei;
verse_text: Therefore have I said: Depart from me, I will weep bitterly: labour not to comfort me, for the devastation of the daughter of my people.

text: A new commandement I giue to you, That you loue one another; as I haue loued you, that you also loue one another.
verse_text: A newe commaundment geve I vnto you that ye love to gedder as I have loved you that even so ye love one another.

text: propter servum meum Jacob, et Israel, electum meum; et vocavi te nomine tuo: assimilavi te, et non cognovisti me.
verse_text: For the sake of my servant Jacob, and Israel my elect, I have even called thee by thy name: I have made a likeness of thee, and thou hast not known me.

text: And the number of the armie of horse-men was twentie thousand times ten thousand. And I heard the number of them.
verse_text: Et numerus equestris exercitus vicies millies dena millia. Et audivi numerum eorum.

text: Be sober and watch: because your aduersarie the Diuel as a roaring lion goeth about, seeking whom he may deuoure.
verse_text: Sobrii estote, et vigilate: quia adversarius vester diabolus tamquam leo rugiens circuit, quaerens quem devoret:

text: Nowe Nebuchad-nezzar King of Babel gaue charge concerning Ieremiah vnto Nebuzar-adan the chiefe stewarde, saying,
verse_text: Now Nabuchodonosor king of Babylon had given charge to Nabuzardan the general concerning Jeremias, saying:

text: And beholde, one came and sayd vnto him, Good Master, what good thing shall I doe, that I may haue eternall life?
verse_text: And behold one came and said to him: Good Maister, what good shal I doe that I may haue life euerlasting?

text: I called to remembrance my song in the night: I communed with mine owne heart, and my spirit searched diligently.
verse_text: ut cognoscat generatio altera: filii qui nascentur et exsurgent, et narrabunt filiis suis,

text: Euery one therfore that shal confesse me before men, I also wil confesse him before my Father which is in Heauen.
verse_text: Therfor euery man that schal knouleche me bifore men, Y schal knouleche hym bifor my fadir that is in heuenes.

text: Go therefore, and teach all nations, baptizing them in the Name of the Father, and the Sonne, and the holy Ghost,
verse_text: Therfor go ye, and teche alle folkis, baptisynge hem in the name of the Fadir, and of the Sone, and of the Hooli Goost;

text: Go therefore, and teach all nations, baptizing them in the Name of the Father, and the Sonne, and the holy Ghost,
verse_text: euntes ergo docete omnes gentes: baptizantes eos in nomine Patris, et Filii, et Spiritus Sancti:

text: In manu artificum opera laudabuntur, et princeps populi in sapientia sermonis sui, in sensu vero seniorum verbum.
verse_text: Works shall be praised for the hand of the artificers, and the prince of the people for the wisdom of his speech, but word of the ancients for the sense.

text: Factum est autem, cum essent filii Israel in solitudine, et invenissent hominem colligentem ligna in die sabbati,
verse_text: And it came to pass, when the children of Israel were in the wilderness, and had found a man gathering sticks on the sabbath day,

text: And they asked him, What then? Art thou Elias? And he said, I am not. Art thou that Prophet? And he answered, No.
verse_text: And thei axiden hym, What thanne? Art thou Elie? And he seide, Y am not. Art thou a profete? And he answeride, Nay.

text: Vnto this houre we both hunger, and thirst, and are naked, and are buffeted, and haue no certaine dwelling place,
verse_text: Usque in hanc horam et esurimus, et sitimus, et nudi sumus, et colaphis caedimur, et instabiles sumus,

text: A new commandement I giue to you, That you loue one another; as I haue loued you, that you also loue one another.
verse_text: Mandatum novum do vobis: ut diligatis invicem: sicut dilexi vos, ut et vos diligatis invicem.

text: For to Moyses he saith: I wil haue mercie on whom I haue mercie; and I wil shew mercie to whom I wil shew mercie.
verse_text: Moysi enim dicit: Miserebor cujus misereor: et misericordiam praestabo cujus miserebor.

text: He is thy praise, and thy God, that hath done for thee these great and terrible things, which thy eyes have seen.
verse_text: He is thi preisyng, and thi God, that made to thee these grete dedis, and ferdful, whiche thin iyen siyen.

text: God no man hath seen at any time: the only-begotten Sonne which is in the bosome of the Father, he hath declared.
verse_text: No man sai euer God, no but the oon bigetun sone, that is in the bosum of the fadir, he hath teld out.

text: And why seest thou the mote, that is in thy brothers eye, and perceiuest not the beame that is in thine owne eye?
verse_text: Quid autem vides festucam in oculo fratris tui, et trabem in oculo tuo non vides?

text: But to euery man that doeth good, shalbe glory, and honour, and peace: to the Iew first, and also to the Grecian.
verse_text: gloria autem, et honor, et pax omni operanti bonum, Judaeo primum, et Graeco:

text: But seeke ye first the kingdome of God, and his righteousnesse, and all these things shall be ministred vnto you.
verse_text: Quaerite ergo primum regnum Dei, et justitiam ejus: et haec omnia adjicientur vobis.

text: But seeke ye first the kingdome of God, and his righteousnesse, and all these things shall be ministred vnto you.
verse_text: But rather seke ye fyrst the kyngdome of heuen and the rightwisnes therof and all these thynges shalbe ministred vnto you.

text: But seeke ye first the kingdome of God, and his righteousnesse, and all these things shall be ministred vnto you.
verse_text: Therfor seke ye first the kyngdom of God, and his riytfulnesse, and alle these thingis shulen be cast to you.

text: Be sober and watch: because your aduersarie the Diuel as a roaring lion goeth about, seeking whom he may deuoure.
verse_text: Be sober and watch for youre adversary the devyll as a rorynge lion walketh about sekynge whom he maye devoure:

text: And why seest thou the mote, that is in thy brothers eye, and perceiuest not the beame that is in thine owne eye?
verse_text: Why seist thou a moote in thy brothers eye and perceavest not the beame that ys yn thyne awne eye.

text: Dixitque David ad Deum: Peccavi nimis ut hoc facerem: obsecro, aufer iniquitatem servi tui, quia insipienter egi.
verse_text: And David said to God: I have sinned exceedingly in doing this: I beseech thee take away the iniquity of thy servant, for I have done foolishly.

text: And from Bamoth in the valley, that is in the plaine of Moab, to the top of Pisgah that looketh toward Ieshimon.
verse_text: De Bamoth, vallis est in regione Moab, in vertice Phasga, quod respicit contra desertum.

text: But hee that keepeth his worde, in him is the loue of God perfect in deede: hereby wee knowe that ye are in him.
verse_text: Qui autem servat verbum ejus, vere in hoc caritas Dei perfecta est: et in hoc scimus quoniam in ipso sumus.

text: Not that we are sufficient of our selues, to thinke any thing, as of our selues: but our sufficiencie is of God,
verse_text: non quod sufficientes simus cogitare aliquid a nobis, quasi ex nobis: sed sufficientia nostra ex Deo est:

text: Not that we are sufficient of our selues, to thinke any thing, as of our selues: but our sufficiencie is of God,
verse_text: not that we are sufficient of oure selves to thinke enythinge as it were of oure selves: but oure ablenes cometh of God

text: As is the earthly, such are they that are earthly: and as is the heauenly, such are they also that are heauenly.
verse_text: Qualis terrenus, tales et terreni: et qualis caelestis, tales et caelestes.

text: Jesus ergo rursum fremens in semetipso, venit ad monumentum. Erat autem spelunca, et lapis superpositus erat ei.
verse_text: Iesus agayne groned in him selfe and came to the grave. It was a caue and a stone layde on it.

text: O God, thou hast cast vs off; thou hast scattered vs, thou hast bene displeased, O turne thy selfe to vs againe.
verse_text: In finem. In hymnis David.

text: O God, thou hast cast vs off; thou hast scattered vs, thou hast bene displeased, O turne thy selfe to vs againe.
verse_text: Vnto the end, in hyms to Dauid.

text: Et statuam eum in domo mea, et in regno meo usque in sempiternum: et thronus ejus erit firmissimus in perpetuum.
verse_text: But I will settle him in my house, and in my kingdom for ever: and his throne shall be most firm for ever.

text: Seuen dayes doe men mourne for him that is dead; but for a foole, and an vngodly man, all the dayes of his life.
verse_text: nequissimi enim nequissima vita super mortem fatui.

text: Porro Absalom fugiens abiit ad Tholomai filium Ammiud regem Gessur. Luxit ergo David filium suum cunctis diebus.
verse_text: But Absalom fled, and went to Tholomai the son of Ammiud the king of Gessur. And David mourned for his son every day.

text: Tulit ergo Israel omnes civitates ejus, et habitavit in urbibus Amorrhaei, in Hesebon scilicet, et viculis ejus.
verse_text: So Israel took all his cities, and dwelt in the cities of the Amorrhite, to wit, in Hesebon, and in the villages thereof.

text: As is the earthly, such are they that are earthly: and as is the heauenly, such are they also that are heauenly.
verse_text: As is the erthy soche are they that are erthye. And as is the hevely soche are they that are hevenly.

text: He shall call vpon me, and I wil heare him: I will be with him in trouble: I will deliuer him, and glorifie him.
verse_text: Adhuc multiplicabuntur in senecta uberi, et bene patientes erunt:

text: Be not yee therefore like vnto them: For your father knoweth what things yee haue neede of, before yee aske him.
verse_text: Therfor nyle ye be maad lich to hem, for your fadir woot what is nede to you, bifore that ye axen hym.

text: Whosoeuer therefore shall confesse mee before men, him will I confesse also before my Father which is in heauen.
verse_text: Therfor euery man that schal knouleche me bifore men, Y schal knouleche hym bifor my fadir that is in heuenes.

text: et percusserunt reliquias, quae evadere potuerant, Amalecitarum, et habitaverunt ibi pro eis usque ad diem hanc.
verse_text: And they slew the remnant of the Amalecites, who had been able to escape, and they dwelt there in their stead unto this day.

text: If therfore thou offer thy guift at the Altar, and there thou remember that thy brother hath ought against thee;
verse_text: Leaue there thine offring before the altar, and goe thy way: first be reconciled to thy brother, and then come and offer thy gift.

text: That thou keepe this commandement without spot, and vnrebukeable, vntill the appearing of our Lord Iesus Christ,
verse_text: ut serves mandatum sine macula, irreprehensibile usque in adventum Domini nostri Jesu Christi,

text: As they passed the tyme in Galile Iesus sayde vnto them: the sonne of man shalbe betrayed into the hondes of men
verse_text: and thei schulen sle hym, and the thridde day he schal rise ayen to lijf.

text: Yea, the darkenes hideth not from thee: but the night shineth as the day: the darkenes and light are both alike.
verse_text: Vir linguosus non dirigetur in terra; virum injustum mala capient in interitu.

text: Our soule is exceedingly filled with the scorning of those that are at ease: and with the contempt of the proud.
verse_text: forsitan aqua absorbuisset nos;

text: And this is life eternall, that they knowe thee to be the onely very God, and whom thou hast sent, Iesus Christ.
verse_text: Haec est autem vita aeterna: ut cognoscant te, solum Deum verum, et quem misisti Jesum Christum.

text: And why seest thou the mote that is in thy brothers eye: and the beame that is in thine owne eye thou seest not?
verse_text: But what seest thou a litil mote in the iye of thi brother, and seest not a beem in thin owne iye?

text: And over against them shall stand on mount Hebal to curse: Ruben, Gad, and Aser, and Zabulon, Dan, and Nephtali.
verse_text: And euene ayens these men schulen stonde in the hil of Hebal to curse, Ruben, Gad, and Aser, Zabulon, Dan, and Neptalym.

text: Manum suam extendit super mare; conturbavit regna. Dominus mandavit adversus Chanaan, ut contereret fortes ejus;
verse_text: He stretched out his hand over the sea, he troubled kingdoms: the Lord hath given a charge against Chanaan, to destroy the strong ones thereof.

text: And this is life eternall, that they knowe thee to be the onely very God, and whom thou hast sent, Iesus Christ.
verse_text: And this is euerlastynge lijf, that thei knowe thee very God aloone, and whom thou hast sent, Jhesu Crist.

text: Quod cum rex annuisset, et obtinuisset principatum, statim ad gentilem ritum contribules suos transferre coepit,
verse_text: Which when the king had granted, and he had gotten the rule into his hands, forthwith he began to bring over his countrymen to the fashion of the heathens.

text: Alia autem ceciderunt in terram bonam: et dabant fructum, aliud centesimum, aliud sexagesimum, aliud trigesimum.
verse_text: Parte fell in good ground and brought forth good frute: some an hundred fold some sixtie fold some thyrty folde.

text: Viri enim Babylonii fecerunt Sochothbenoth: viri autem Cuthaei fecerunt Nergel: et viri de Emath fecerunt Asima.
verse_text: For the men of Babylon made Sochothbenoth: and the Cuthites made Nergel: and the men of Emath made Asima.

text: Cumque omnes dixissent: Amen: accesserunt ad convivium: sed et cum timore Domini nuptiarum convivium exercebant.
verse_text: And when all had said, Amen, they went to the feast: but the marriage feast they celebrated also with the fear of the Lord.

text: And to euery one that asketh thee, giue, and of him that taketh away the things that are thine, aske not againe.
verse_text: Geve to every man that axeth of the. And of him that taketh awaye thy goodes axe them not agayne.

text: Take also ye summe of the sonnes of Gershon, euery one by the houses of their fathers throughout their families:
verse_text: Take the sum of the soils of Gerson also by their houses and families and kindreds.

text: Take also ye summe of the sonnes of Gershon, euery one by the houses of their fathers throughout their families:
verse_text: Tolle summam etiam filiorum Gerson per domos ac familias et cognationes suas,

text: And I say to you, Aske, and it shal be giuen you: seeke, and you shal find: knock, and it shal be opened to you.
verse_text: Et ego dico vobis: Petite, et dabitur vobis; quaerite, et invenietis; pulsate, et aperietur vobis.

text: And Herod said: Iohn I haue beheaded; but who is this of whom I heare such things? And he sought for to see him.
verse_text: And Eroude seide, Y haue biheedid Joon; and who is this, of whom Y here siche thingis? And he souyte to se hym.

text: And I say to you, Aske, and it shal be giuen you: seeke, and you shal find: knock, and it shal be opened to you.
verse_text: And Y seie to you, axe ye, and it schal be youun to you; seke ye, and ye schulen fynde; knocke ye, and it schal be openyd to you.

text: And I say to you, Aske, and it shal be giuen you: seeke, and you shal find: knock, and it shal be opened to you.
verse_text: And I saye vnto you: axe and it shalbe geven you. Seke and ye shall fynde. knocke and it shalbe opened vnto you.

text: Knowing that he which hath raised vp the Lord Iesus, shall raise vs vp also by Iesus, and shall set vs with you.
verse_text: scientes quoniam qui suscitavit Jesum, et nos cum Jesu suscitabit, et constituet vobiscum.

text: For euery one that asketh, receiueth: and he that seeketh, findeth: and to him that knocketh, it shal be opened.
verse_text: For ech that axith, takith, and he that sekith, fyndith; and to a man that knockith, it schal be openyd.

text: And to our deare sister Apphia, and to Archippus our fellowe souldier, and to the Church that is in thine house:
verse_text: and to the beloved Appia and to Archippus oure felowe soudier and to the congregacion of thy housse.

text: Now therfore ye are no moare straugers and foreners: but citesyns with the saynctes and of the housholde of god:
verse_text: Now therefore yee are no more strangers and forreiners; but fellow citizens with the Saints, and of the houshold of God,

text: et in Bethmarchaboth, et in Hasarsusim, et in Bethberai, et in Saarim: hae civitates eorum usque ad regem David.
verse_text: And in Bethmarchaboth, and in Hasarsusim, and in Bethberai, and in Saarim. These were their cities unto the reign of David.

text: And why seest thou the mote that is in thy brothers eye: and the beame that is in thine owne eye thou seest not?

text: Ego feci terram, et hominem super eam creavi ego: manus meae tetenderunt caelos, et omni militiae eorum mandavi.
verse_text: I made the earth: and I created man upon it: my hand stretched forth the heavens, and I have commanded all their host.

text: Et mortuus est in senectute bona, plenus dierum, et divitiis, et gloria: et regnavit Salomon filius ejus pro eo.
verse_text: And he died in a good age, full of days, and riches, and glory. And Solomon his son reigned in his stead.

text: And I giue vnto them eternall life, and they shall neuer perish, neither shall any plucke them out of mine hand.

text: Therefore also after that I heard of the faith, which ye haue in the Lord Iesus, and loue toward all the Saints,

text: And I giue vnto them eternall life, and they shall neuer perish, neither shall any plucke them out of mine hand.
verse_text: et ego vitam aeternam do eis, et non peribunt in aeternum, et non rapiet eas quisquam de manu mea.

text: Iesus saide vnto her, Saide I not vnto thee, that if thou diddest beleeue, thou shouldest see the glorie of God?

verse_text: And he sayde vnto them: is the candle lighted to be put vnder a busshell or vnder the table and not rather to be put on a candelstick?

text: Whosoever kepeth his (worde) in him is the love of god parfect in dede. And therby knowe we that we are in him.
verse_text: But who so keepeth his word, in him verely is the loue of God perfected: hereby know we that we are in him.

text: Can any man forbid water, that these should not be baptized, which haue receiued the holy Ghost, as well as we?

text: Whosoeuer therefore shall confesse me before men, him will I confesse also before my Father which is in heauen.

text: Sed in ecclesia volo quinque verba sensu meo loqui, ut et alios instruam: quam decem millia verborum in lingua.

text: Then Iesus answered, and sayd vnto them, They that are whole, neede not the Physician, but they that are sicke.
verse_text: Iesus answered and sayde vnto the: They that are whole nede not of the phisicion: but they that are sicke.

text: And certaine of the Pharises sayde vnto them, Why doe ye that which is not lawfull to doe on the Sabbath dayes?
verse_text: And certayne of the Pharises sayde vnto them: Why do the that which is not laufull to do on the saboth dayes?

text: The sonnes of Beriah were, of Heber the familie of the Heberites: of Malchiel, the familie of the Malchielites.

text: Remember that Iesus Christ, made of the seede of Dauid, was raysed againe from the dead according to my Gospel,

text: Nether shewed I my selfe that I knewe eny thinge amonge you save Iesus Christ even the same that was crucified.
verse_text: For I esteemed not to knowe any thing among you, saue Iesus Christ, and him crucified.

text: Appellavit autem Nehemias hunc locum Nephthar, quod interpretatur Purificatio: vocatur autem apud plures Nephi.
verse_text: And Nehemias called this place Nephthar, which is interpreted purification. But many call it Nephi.

text: A litle while, and ye shall not see me: and againe a litle while, and ye shall see me: for I goe to the Father.

text: Let not a widow be taken into the number vnder three score yeere olde, that hath beene the wife of one husband,

text: Let not a widow be taken into the number vnder three score yeere olde, that hath beene the wife of one husband,
verse_text: Let no wyddowe be chosen vnder threscore yere olde and soche a one as was the wyfe of one man

text: Paul an Apostle of Iesus Christ, by the will of God, according to the promise of life which is in Christ Iesus,

text: For I count that the afflictions of this present time are not worthy of the glory, which shalbe shewed vnto vs.

text: De magnis periculis a Deo liberati, magnifice gratias agimus ipsi, utpote qui adversus talem regem dimicavimus.

text: Strengthened with all might through his glorious power, vnto all patience, and long suffering with ioyfulnesse,

text: Lest there should be any diuision in the body: but that the members shoulde haue the same care one for another.

text: And seing the multitudes, he pitied them; because they were vexed, and lay like sheep that haue not a shepeard.

text: Yet a litle while, and the world shall see me no more, but ye shall see me: because I liue, ye shall liue also.

verse_text: And he sayde vnto me: happy are they which are called vnto the Lambes supper. And he sayde vnto me: these are the true sayinges of God.

text: For whosoeuer will saue his life, shall lose it: and whosoeuer shall lose his life for my sake, shall finde it.
verse_text: For who soever wyll save his lyfe shall loose it. And whosoever shall loose his lyfe for my sake shall fynde it.

text: I call to remembrance my song in the night: I commune with mine owne heart, and my spirit made diligent search.

text: Sed nec ipse Juda custodivit mandata Domini Dei sui: verum ambulavit in erroribus Israel, quos operatus fuerat.
verse_text: But neither did Juda itself keep the commandments of the Lord their God: but they walked in the errors of Israel, which they had wrought.

text: Yee are all the children of light, and the children of the day: we are not of the night, neither of darkenesse.

text: The life of a labourer that is content with what he hath, shall be sweet, and in it thou shalt find a treasure.

text: And the beast that was, and is not, is euen the eight, and is one of the seuen, and shall goe into destruction.

text: So are ye also: for outwarde ye appeare righteous vnto men, but within ye are full of hypocrisie and iniquitie.
verse_text: So are ye for outwarde ye appere righteous vnto me when within ye are full of ypocrisie and iniquite.

text: When sinners shal spring vp as grasse: and al that worke iniquitie shal appeare. That they may perish for euer:
verse_text: Doubtlesse with thine eyes shalt thou beholde and see the reward of the wicked.

text: He shal crie to me, and I wil heare him: with him I am in tribulation: I wil deliuer him, and wil glorifie him.
verse_text: Comfort vs according to the dayes that thou hast afflicted vs, and according to the yeeres that we haue seene euill.

text: Ad dexteram enim et ad laevam penetrabis, et semen tuum gentes haereditabit, et civitates desertas inhabitabit.
verse_text: For thou shalt pass on to the right hand, and to the left: and thy seed shall inherit the Gentiles, and shall inhabit the desolate cities.

text: For we preache not oure selves but Christ Iesus to be the Lorde and oure selves youre servautes for Iesus sake.
verse_text: For we preach not our selues, but Christ Iesus the Lord, and our selues your seruants for Iesus sake.

text: My soule thirsteth for God, euen for the liuing God: when shall I come and appeare before the presence of God?

text: As a corne of seneuei, which whanne it is sowun in the erthe, is lesse than alle seedis that ben in the erthe;
verse_text: It is lyke a grayne of mustard seed which when it is sowe in the erth is the leest of all seedes that be in the erth:

text: For though I bee free from all men, yet haue I made my selfe seruant vnto all men, that I might winne the moe.

text: not that we be sufficient to thinke any thing of our-selues, as of our-selues: but our sufficiencie is of God.

text: Take heede to your selues: if thy brother trespasse against thee, rebuke him: and if hee repent, forgiue him.
